##Take-out orders in Wuhan: through the isolation of love, affection and courage

Wechat, renwumag1980

Feature Introduction, the best Chinese character report

On New Year's Eve, as the epidemic spread, the city of Wuhan was closed, the airport, railway station, the city's public transport was closed, and Wuhan was besieged. Since the city's closure, many people in Wuhan have suffered separation, fearing that their elderly parents, who live alone, can not buy food, bemoaning the fact that their loved ones can not be with them when they need it most. Fathers who have worked away for years have missed the only chance to see their children.
An epidemic can isolate space, but it can not isolate love. Now in Wuhan, a secret passageway is being built to link the outside world. Over the past week, more than 200,000 orders have been sent to Wuhan on Alibaba's platform, from migrant daughters buying food for elderly people with mobility problems and from stranded fathers giving their sons New Year gifts.
These loving tasks, all fell on the streets of the delivery rider, in their eyes, you can see a not isolated Wuhan.

Roses for Mama

According to Alibaba, 30,000 of the "out-of-town orders" for takeout in Wuhan are for the elderly. The next single people are far away, under the epidemic of the Spring Festival, Wuhan is they want to go home but can not go back, and stay in the city's parents, is the deepest concern in their hearts.

DICTATION RIDER: Feng Qingyuan, Male, 40

Shortly before the Spring Festival, I went home, and then came back to continue to work overtime, twenty-nine morning, just got up, saw the news said Wuhan to close the city, think of the old people at home, simply stay, do not take the danger back.

Did Not go home for the New Year, many people have called me, parents, brothers and sisters, even long-lost distant relatives have called to greet, the daughter is a morning or evening a phone "supervision" me.

In fact, the beginning of fear, come back from work in bed, always insomnia, to five or six in the morning to sleep. And then I thought, well, doctors are first-line, and we're second-line delivery guys, and I can't get out, and somebody really can't.

The streets of Wuhan are empty, sometimes a person riding on the road, think of those people and things these days, not too bad.

I got a box-horse order the other day, delivering fruit and vegetables to a couple of old people. The clerk told me that this is a special treatment of customer service, the order is a woman more than 40, people in Shanghai can not come back, Wuhan home only two old people living together.

Unable to buy anything, the two old men had been eating leftovers for days. The clerk told me that the woman had cried on the phone. It was urgent.

UPSTAIRS, the door is an old man, gray hair, some rickets body, through the mask hurriedly said thank you, but also forced to give me two masks. Later, I heard that the lady also made a special call to thank customer service, are sons and daughters, her mood I know.

This job that I'm doing, it's always been so mundane and trivial, but at this particular moment, suddenly something really meaningful happens to me. Many orders have special notes on them.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Recently in Wuhan's hungry, Hema orders will have similar remarks

Such remarks as exhortation to wear a mask, there are some clear purpose, you can see behind the children's anxiety, I can tell the elderly. Some notes have no immediate purpose, such as "FOR MOM and dad! Please. " , "hard, parents alone at home, we can not come back outside" , "hard, Wuhan closed city, can not come back to see mom and dad. "

At first I thought, what's the point of them writing this, and what can I do?

Later, I figured out that they were helpless, ah, Miss Their parents, and do not know where to say, had to write to me this will see their parents to see people, to give their own comfort. So every time after carrying these things out to give, always feel heavy, feel different meaning, they are not only objects, but also feelings.

A young man in Shandong Province sent 84 disinfectant to his home in Wuhan. A young girl in Beijing would call me and tell me to look for more roads in the past, because the neighborhood is not easy to walk in, she didn't hang up until it arrived, and a daughter in Hefei, Anhui Province, bought her mother a bouquet of bright red roses.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"please tell your boyfriend I miss you. "

The outbreak has isolated families, friends and lovers both inside and outside Wuhan. During this time, they had to endure not being able to see each other. But the outbreak did not cut them off from each other, and many people sent their concerns to friends and partners in Wuhan by placing orders in different places. Wuhan is also passing out their own voice, although in the city, Wuhan users are still in the first three days, to the field of relatives and friends to feed 3995 single.

Dictation Rider: Kang Zhuoyu, 33

Around three o'clock in the afternoon of the second day, I received an order to go to the supermarket to get things, a closer look, things are really many, I guess I can not finish a car.

I glanced at the note again, and was a little moved by it. It said, "hello, this is for my friend. She's here for medical assistance. I don't know the room number. Please send it to me. Thank you. ". "

I soon found the supermarket. All the other stores were closed, and this one was the only one standing on the long street. The order was filled with food, milk, biscuits, rice pudding, and three boxes of Yibao mineral water, one of which I placed on the front pedal because I didn't need to keep it warm.

The streets of Wuhan had never been so empty. There was not a single pedestrian in sight, except for the occasional car. The destination is not far, three kilometers, the former 161 hospital, now the central war zone General Hospital, I have to send things to the hotel next door, here is now also isolated to treat patients.

Things can only be delivered to the door, to call the consignee in the past, to answer the phone is a thin voice of a girl, after a long while, she just came out of the building, I immediately looked surprised: small and exquisite stature, full military uniform.

I saw something heavy, so I talked from a distance in my mask, and I wanted to take it for her. She thanked me and said she could move it in batches, but I couldn't go in. Looking at her small back, I understand, the distance that cares about her boy why so anxious.

Hungry riders deliver meals to first-line medical workers in Wuhan.

You know, there's a lot of stories like that on the list.

A girl in Guangzhou ordered a braised chicken rice for her boyfriend in Wuhan. She wrote in a note: "today is my boyfriend's birthday. Please say happy birthday to me when the delivery boy arrives. "! Long-distance relationship and closed city, the boyfriend a long time to eat instant noodles. "

Another friend from Guangzhou also ordered at the small Sichuan home-cooked restaurant: "I was out of town and worried my girlfriend wouldn't be able to eat alone in Wuhan. ". "

I also took on a very difficult job, is a girl in Zhejiang Province to Wuhan's boyfriend to buy fruit, but the remarks in a special request: Please say I miss you.

All the way I have been thinking, how to say this sentence, and whether to say it, not to say it will not have any effect, I feel a little ashamed.

When I got to the neighborhood and couldn't get in, I waited for someone to come out and pick it up. I saw a boy coming from a distance. He was wearing socks, slippers, black-rimmed glasses and unshaven.

He took it, turned away, took two steps and suddenly stopped, muttering, "thank you for your hard work. ". " then I called out to him, saying, "your girlfriend asked me to tell you that she misses you. " He listened, grinning, and said, "thank you. "

"For the heroes of the line, please cut up all the boss! "

On this special day, tens of thousands of users in the takeaway order notes to the city of Wuhan refueling, blessing. Among them, the remarks "Wuhan Refueling" , "blessing Wuhan" orders more than 80% from Shanghai, Beijing, Hangzhou and more than 200 cities. Meanwhile, riders received more than 60,000 orders for takeout similar to those sent to the Wuhan anti-epidemic Front.

Dictation Rider: Liu Junwu, 42

I am a native of Henan Province, my wife's hometown is in Hubei Province, my mother-in-law raised my children here. After graduating from high school, I struggled around for more than 20 years, and ended up in Wuhan, where I became a hungry horse rider, earning more than the previous factory.

Originally the Spring Festival also did not intend to go home, thought that has the subsidy, may earn many points, again meets the epidemic situation, had to step up the work.

My station, there is a special task, every day to the nearby south-central hospital delivery of two meals, more than 300 meals, we eight riders, led by the Stationmaster, take turns, each time to come back to the whole body disinfection.

Since the outbreak of the disease in Wuhan, people all over the country have extended their hands to help. Before that, they all saw on the news that some people donated money and some people donated materials. I did not expect that I would have the opportunity to experience this firsthand. Although the city of Wuhan closed, but everyone's love is not cut off, for this I have the experience.

Because of the proximity to the hospital, we often receive some special out-of-town orders. The other party is to order a thing, neither to family members, nor to friends, but to care about those first-line medical staff, they do not specify who, just said to the hospital.

These nameless love hearts are particularly touching. I was originally going to the hospital, so whenever I received this kind of "love order" , I would put it directly into the original food and send it together, thus satisfying the wishes of netizens to show their love, keep the list, and it won't go to waste if you can't find someone to take it.

These orders from all over the country, there will be a long note, express their concern for Wuhan and the first-line medical staff.

"I am from Anxi County, in Anxi County, with the people of Wuhan. Come on! To the doctors and nurses at the hospital."

"This is a concern from Chengdu. I hope everyone in the medical staff is well. Don't call me. Just put it at the front desk. Thank you. "

"I'm from Tianjin. Please help me send you the dumplings you like! New Year's Eve so that medical staff can eat dumplings! Go Wuhan! "

"from Nanjing, boss, please follow your Wuhan Taste! "! "

"The Gansu Compatriots refuels for Wuhan, fights in the front line heroic people, you worked hard, troublesome boss all cuts the block! "! "

Although things are not much, but behind every delivery, are real passion, I go to achieve them, just a small effort, the heart is the most important.

"Daddy loves YOU WITH ALL HIS HEART. "

At the moment still in Wuhan Street delivery riders, many are outsiders. Because of the closure of the city, this Spring Festival they can not be reunited with their families, many care about family orders in different places, can not help but stir up waves in their hearts. Fortunately, some of them do.

Dictation Rider: Sun Qingtian, 28

My son is two years old this year, originally intended to go home for the New Year, later Wuhan closed the city, can not go back, just a person stay in the rental house, with home video every day, Miss Them Ah.

While it's risky to run around all day, it's also rewarding to have something that no one else has. More than once I've seen people give me the thumbs-up and yell "Go" as I've been cycling down the street.

Someone will give me a mask, someone asked me to buy things, but also specifically told me, do not force, can not buy it does not matter, pay attention to their safety. This kind of stranger care, really, to be honest, it's been kind of a long time coming.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In fact, being in my position, I can feel the feelings that people don't show at ordinary times.

That day, I sent a piece of fruit, which was bought by a big sister in Beijing. The tone in the message was that of a northern girl, who was called "big sister or big brother. " He also specifically told the merchants to wash and cut the fruit well, "my family's wife" would not.

It was a short walk, a few minutes away, and it was a new neighborhood, with Shiny Black Iron Gates. Security pulled me over, said I couldn't get in, had to call the receiver. It took three calls to get through. It was a thick voice. The other party was busy, just put it in the guard's room and hung up after saying thanks. The sound over there is a little bit mixed, like in the hospital, no wonder, will be so worried about people.

There is a list I sent particularly strong, is a cup of milk tea, but there is a very special demand, to paint a small shop Peqi pigs. I sat there waiting, the clerk is a young girl, she in the counter pondered for a long time, finally in the White Paper draw a simple peggy, small, some deformation, but also pretty cute.

Couldn't get into the neighborhood, called each other, a woman answered, and there were kids yelling, "Daddy! ". I thought my son was home too, I couldn't go back to see him, and I was pretty sore about it.

A father in Ensch, Hubei Province, bought his son a big pile of snacks at Qianji Kengee Star harbor store. The note to the order read: "Happy New Year, take care of yourself, although you can't come back, but daddy loves you with all his heart, BOSCO BOSCO! "! "

I was quite impressed by the food I had brought to a little girl. I left it in the gatehouse and stood far away waiting for her to come and get it. A bespectacled girl, wrapped in a scarf, walked with her hands folded in front of her, looking cold.

She saw me in my jockey uniform from a distance and gave me a slight nod. The note to the order reads: "My sister was alone in Wuhan and ordered something for her. Thanks to the riders! "

"Happy New Year. I'm fine. "

People inside and outside Wuhan Express different concerns through take-out orders. Through the order content and remarks, the outside world can be a glimpse of the epidemic, the warmth of Wuhan throughout the country.

People sent to Wuhan Friends take-out orders, notes there are more than 4,000"attention to the epidemic" , more than 5,000"Wuhan Refueling" ..

For example, these days, people in Wuhan receive thousands of pairs of playing cards, chess and backgammon through takeout, and more than 100 orders have a note that reads, "don't go out! "! "

Alibaba's data also shows that even in an epidemic area, many people in Wuhan still remember a good years. People in Wuhan ordered more than 1,000 takeout orders to each other and left messages: "Happy New Year" and "happy New Year" .

There are even more than 300 users in Wuhan, calling it a take out order -- as if
